## Part 3: Architecture & Implementation (25%)

### 3.1 OpenFOAM Class Hierarchy for FVM

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class polyMesh {
        +points()
        +faces()
        +cells()
        - Geometric primitives
    }

    class lduMesh {
        +lduAddr()
        +interfaces()
        - Linear algebra structure
    }

    class surfaceInterpolation {
        +interpolate()
        - Face interpolation methods
    }

    class fvMesh {
        +V() : cell volumes
        +Sf() : face area vectors
        +C() : cell centers
        +Cf() : face centers
        +owner() : face owners
        +neighbour() : face neighbours
        # Finite volume discretization
    }

    class fvSchemes {
        +ddtSchemes_
        +gradSchemes_
        +divSchemes_
        +laplacianSchemes_
        # Scheme selectors
    }

    class gradScheme~Type~ {
        <<abstract>>
        +grad(Field)
    }

    class gaussGrad {
        +gradf() : surface field gradient
        +calcGrad() : volume field gradient
        # Gauss theorem implementation
    }

    class divScheme~Type~ {
        <<abstract>>
        +fvcDiv()
    }

    class gaussDivScheme {
        +fvcDiv() : explicit divergence
        # Gauss theorem implementation
    }

    polyMesh <|-- fvMesh
    lduMesh <|-- fvMesh
    surfaceInterpolation <|-- fvMesh
    fvMesh *-- fvSchemes : uses
    gradScheme <|-- gaussGrad
    divScheme <|-- gaussDivScheme
    fvSchemes --> gradScheme : instantiates
    fvSchemes --> divScheme : instantiates
```

### 3.2 fvSchemes Configuration System

> ⭐ **Verified from `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/fvSchemes/fvSchemes.H`**
>
> The `fvSchemes` class is a selector class for finite volume differencing schemes. It contains:
> - `ddtSchemes_`: Temporal discretization schemes
> - `divSchemes_`: Divergence schemes using Gauss theorem
> - `gradSchemes_`: Gradient schemes using Gauss theorem
> - `laplacianSchemes_`: Laplacian schemes
> - `interpolationSchemes_`: Face interpolation schemes

**Example Configuration** (`system/fvSchemes`):

```cpp
gradSchemes
{
    default         Gauss linear;          // ⭐ Basic second-order gradient
    grad(p)         Gauss linear;          // Pressure gradient
    grad(U)         Gauss linear;          // Velocity gradient
}

divSchemes
{
    default         none;
    div(phi,U)      Gauss linearUpwind grad(U);  // Convection
    div(phi,k)      Gauss limitedLinear 1;       // Turbulence
    div(phi,omega)  Gauss limitedLinear 1;
}

laplacianSchemes
{
    default         Gauss linear corrected;  // Diffusion
}
```

**Scheme Selection Mechanism:**
1. `fvSchemes` dictionary read at runtime
2. Scheme factories create appropriate discretization objects
3. `gaussGrad` selected for "Gauss linear"
4. Face interpolation method specified after "Gauss"

### 3.3 Gauss Gradient Implementation Walkthrough

> ⭐ **Verified from `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/gradSchemes/gaussGrad/gaussGrad.H`**
>
> The `gaussGrad` class is a basic second-order gradient scheme using face-interpolation and Gauss' theorem. Key methods:
> - `gradf()`: Return gradient using Gauss' theorem on surface field (lines 36-96)
> - `calcGrad()`: Calculate gradient of volField (lines 99-121)

**Algorithm Overview:**

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Input: volScalarField phi] --> B[Interpolate to Faces]
    B --> C[phi_f = interpolate(phi)]
    C --> D[Initialize Gradient Field<br>gradPhi = 0]
    D --> E{Loop Faces}
    E --> F[Internal Faces]
    E --> G[Boundary Faces]

    F --> H[Owner: +phi_f*Sf]
    F --> I[Neighbor: -phi_f*Sf]

    G --> J[Boundary Contribution<br>phi_{bf}*Sf]

    H --> K[Accumulate]
    I --> K
    J --> K

    K --> L[Normalize: /V_cell]
    L --> M[Correct Boundary Conditions]
    M --> N[Output: volVectorField gradPhi]

    style H fill:#e1f5fe
    style I fill:#e1f5fe
    style J fill:#f3e5f5
```

**Key Code Snippets with Analysis:**

> **File:** `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/gradSchemes/gaussGrad/gaussGrad.C`
> **Lines:** 70-76
> **Internal Face Loop:**
> ```cpp
> forAll(owner, facei)
> {
>     GradType Sfssf = Sf[facei]*issf[facei];
>
>     igGrad[owner[facei]] += Sfssf;
>     igGrad[neighbour[facei]] -= Sfssf;
> }
> ```
>
> **Analysis:**
> - Line 72: Computes product $\mathbf{S}_f \phi_f$ for current face
> - Line 74: Owner cell **adds** contribution (normal points from owner to neighbor)
> - Line 75: Neighbor cell **subtracts** contribution (outward normal convention)
> - This ensures exact conservation of flux

> **File:** `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/gradSchemes/gaussGrad/gaussGrad.C`
> **Lines:** 78-89
> **Boundary Face Loop:**
> ```cpp
> forAll(mesh.boundary(), patchi)
> {
>     const fvPatch& p = mesh.boundary()[patchi];
>     const labelUList& pFaceCells = p.faceCells();
>     const vectorField& pSf = mesh.Sf().boundaryField()[patchi];
>     const fvsPatchField<Type>& pssf = ssf.boundaryField()[patchi];
>
>     forAll(p, facei)
>     {
>         igGrad[pFaceCells[facei]] += pSf[facei]*pssf[facei];
>     }
> }
> ```
>
> **Analysis:**
> - Loops over all boundary patches
> - Gets face-cell addressing for boundary
> - Boundary faces only contribute to their adjacent cell (owner)
> - No neighbor cell for boundary faces

> **File:** `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/gradSchemes/gaussGrad/gaussGrad.C`
> **Line:** 91
> **Volume Normalization:**
> ```cpp
> igGrad /= mesh.V();
> ```
>
> **Analysis:**
> - Divides accumulated surface sum by cell volume
> - Implements the $\frac{1}{V_P}$ factor in the discrete gradient formula
> - Performed element-wise on all cells

**Mathematical Correspondence:**

The code implements exactly:
$$
\nabla \phi |_P = \frac{1}{V_P} \sum_{f \in F(P)} \phi_f \mathbf{S}_f
$$

where $F(P)$ are faces of cell $P$.

### 3.4 Complete Implementation Example

**Full Gradient Calculation Workflow:**

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant calcGrad
    participant interpolate
    participant gradf
    participant Mesh

    User->>calcGrad: fvc::grad(phi)
    calcGrad->>interpolate: Interpolate phi to faces
    interpolate-->>calcGrad: SurfaceField phi_f

    calcGrad->>gradf: gradf(phi_f, name)
    gradf->>Mesh: Get owner(), neighbour(), Sf()
    Mesh-->>gradf: Mesh data

    loop Internal Faces
        gradf->>gradf: Owner += phi_f * Sf
        gradf->>gradf: Neighbor -= phi_f * Sf
    end

    loop Boundary Faces
        gradf->>gradf: Cell += phi_bf * Sf_bf
    end

    gradf->>Mesh: Get V() for normalization
    Mesh-->>gradf: Cell volumes
    gradf->>gradf: igGrad /= V()

    gradf-->>calcGrad: volVectorField gradPhi
    calcGrad-->>User: Gradient field
```

